.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH ox-cancel 1  "ox-cancel " 
.SH NAME
ox\-cancel \- Cancel running jobs
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBox\-cancel\fR [\fB\-\-all\fR] [\fB\-\-where\fR] [\fB\-\-rule\fR] [\fB\-\-session\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-file\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fINAMES\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Cancel running jobs
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Cancel ALL running and pending jobs
.TP
\fB\-\-where\fR \fI<KEY=VALUE>\fR
Filter by tag (KEY=VALUE)
.TP
\fB\-\-rule\fR \fI<RULE>\fR
Cancel only jobs for this rule
.TP
\fB\-\-session\fR \fI<SESSION>\fR
Cancel only jobs in this session
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output JSON
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fI<FILE>\fR [default: Oxymakefile.toml]
Oxymakefile path
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
[\fINAMES\fR]
Job names to cancel (cancels each job and its downstream dependents).

Accepts job IDs (e.g. `call\-sample01`) or output file paths. When omitted, use \-\-all or \-\-rule to select jobs.
